These topics are typically covered in the following arXiv CS sub-categories: cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.LM (Logic in Machine Learning), and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of comonads, which are a categorical concept, further supporting the inclusion of cs.LO and cs.PL as likely sub-categories.
